HARARE – Zimbabwe President Robert Mugabe has left his private home to meet with a South Africa delegation at State House.  The motorcade reportedly left his private residence in Borrowdale, Harare at 10am on Thursday. READ: Zimbabwe in turmoil Zimbabwe was on a knife's edge on Wednesday after the army seized power in an apparent military coup. The army insisted that Mugabe was safe and was not a target of its actions. READ: 10 things you didn't know about Robert Mugabe The defence force demanded an end to the purges in the ruling party, Zanu-PF. It came after vice president Emmerson Mnangagwa was fired by Mugabe last week. President Jacob Zuma on Wednesday announced that he would send special envoys, Minister of Defence and Military Veterans Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula and the Minister of State Security Bongani Bongo, to the neighbouring country to meet with Mugabe and the Zimbabwean Defence Force. eNCA